### Error format [GET /error]

This document describes standard error responses for reuse.

#### Response processing

* [Response.error.code]: Error code for client
* [Response.error.message]: Error message for client
* [Response.error.details]: Error details (optional, only for 422 and 429)
    * For 422 (Validation): Array of field-level errors
        * [Response.error.details[].field]: Field name that failed validation  
        * [Response.error.details[].message]: Specific error message for the field
    * For 429 (Rate Limit): Object with rate limiting information
        * [Response.error.details.retry_after]: Seconds to wait before retry
        * [Response.error.details.limit]: Rate limit threshold
        * [Response.error.details.remaining]: Remaining requests  
        * [Response.error.details.reset]: Reset timestamp

#### Error code definitions

| HTTP status code | When to use | Examples |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 400 Bad Request | Request has invalid technical format | - Malformed JSON (parse error)<br />- Wrong Content-Type<br />- Missing request body when required<br />- Field has wrong data type (string instead of number) |
| 401 Unauthorized | Not properly authenticated | - Missing or invalid Authorization header<br />- Token expired / revoked<br />- Invalid JWT signature |
| 403 Forbidden | Authenticated but not authorized | - Missing required role / scope<br />- Attempting to access resource outside allowed boundary (different tenant)<br />- Blocked by policy (e.g. account locked) |
| 404 Not Found | Resource does not exist (or is concealed for security) | - ID not found<br />- Endpoint does not exist (possibly framework-generated 404) |
| 422 Unprocessable Entity | Payload is valid JSON but fails validation | - Missing required field<br />- Field violates pattern / format (email, enum, length)<br />- Other business validation errors (e.g. attempt to cancel an already delivered order) |
| 429 Too Many Requests | Exceeded rate limit or quota | - More than environment variable value [RATE_LIMIT_PER_IP_PER_MINUTE] requests per minute per IP<br />- More than environment variable value [RATE_LIMIT_PER_USER_PER_HOUR] requests per hour per authenticated user<br />- Burst limit: More than environment variable value [RATE_LIMIT_PER_SECOND] requests per second |
| 500 Internal Server Error | Unexpected server-side error | - Unhandled exception<br />- System / infrastructure failure (DB, cache, internal service)<br />- Other uncategorized error |

+ Response 400 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + request_id: `a1c7f92d-5f1b-4f09-9e3d-1e2f7e8b2c11` (string, required) - Request ID
        + success: false (boolean, required) - Request success flag
        + timestamp: `2025-01-15T10:05:23.412Z` (string, required) - Request timestamp
        + error (object, required) - Error information
            + code: `REQUEST_FORMAT_ERROR` (string, required) - Code
            + message: `Invalid request format` (string, required) - Message

